cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the use of machine learning components in cyber-physical systems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on machine learning and deep neural networks suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The use of these components in control systems suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with safety concerns, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of simulation for self-driving cars suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category. Finally, the use of anomaly detection and conformal prediction suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category.
